title: Colonel Quaritch, V.C.: A Tale of Country Life
creator: H. Rider Haggard
description: Librivox recording of Colonel Quaritch, V.C.: A Tale of Country Life by H. Rider Haggard read by Esther. This is not your typical H. Rider Haggard adventure book yet it is full of mystery and intrigue including a coerced marriage, bigotry, adultery, murder and a buried treasure! This is the tale of an ancient family’s struggles to survive, one woman’s selflessness and another’s evil schemes; Two Gentlemen, two scoundrels and one very underestimated, loyal servant. Listen as the tale unfolds and guess where the treasure is hidden that can save them all! Summary by Esther. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audiobooks or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org M4B format available
subject: librivox;  audiobook;  literature; romance; intrigue; treasure
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: I really enjoyed this story.  I was rooting for Colonel Quaritch through the story, he is a very loveable guy.  The narration was pretty good too if I remember.  Good story worth listening to.
